DescriptionInternal__c: Designed for everyday transactions. It provides a secure place to deposit money, and account holders can easily access and manage their funds for various financial transactions
Name: Current Account

DescriptionInternal__c: A bank account designed to help individuals save and earn interest on their money
Name: Savings Account

DescriptionInternal__c: A type of mortgage arrangement that integrates a mortgage loan with a savings or current account resulting in reduced interest payments and a shorter repayment period
Name: Offset Mortgage Cash Account

DescriptionInternal__c: A savings product offered by National Savings and Investments (NS&I), which is a UK government-backed savings institution. Premium Bonds differ from traditional savings accounts in that they do not pay regular interest. Instead, the interest is replaced by a monthly prize draw where bondholders have the chance to win tax-free cash prizes
Name: NS&I Premium Bond

DescriptionInternal__c: 1 year fixed rate, will pay out interest after the year
Name: Guaranteed Growth Bond

DescriptionInternal__c: 1 year fixed rate, will pay out interest after the year. Pays monthly income
Name: Guaranteed Income Bond

DescriptionInternal__c: Money for green project, annual fixed interest rate over 3 year term. Interest will always be 3 years
Name: NS&I Green Savings Bond

DescriptionInternal__c: available for 2 or 5 year period at a fixed rate - no longer available to take out but people who hold can reinvest
Name: NS&I Savings Certificate (Fixed Rate)

DescriptionInternal__c: 3-5 years linked to inflation -  no longer available to take out but people who hold can reinvest
Name: NS&I Savings Certificate (Index Linked)
